# CLAUDE.md

## Build commands

```bash
zig build            # Build examples + run all tests (default step)
zig build test       # Run unit tests + integration tests
zig build test-shell-completions  # Test shell completion scripts (requires fish, zsh, expect)
```

## Project structure

```
src/
  zap.zig            # Public API: CommandMeta, Positional, run(), parseFromSlice()
  parser.zig         # Argument parsing (maps tokens to struct fields)
  help.zig           # Help text generation, camelToKebab naming
  introspect.zig     # Comptime struct introspection (ArgInfo, ArgKind)
  tokenizer.zig      # Argv tokenizer (long/short flags, options, positionals, terminators)
  errors.zig         # Error types, Levenshtein distance, typo suggestions
  complete.zig       # Shell completion entry point (Shell, CompletionHint)
  complete/
    fish.zig         # Fish shell completion generation
    zsh.zig          # Zsh shell completion generation
    bash.zig         # Bash shell completion generation
example/
  add.zig            # Simple single-command demo (flags, multi-positional)
  math.zig           # Subcommand demo (add, multiply)
  shell-completion.zig  # Full-featured demo (enums, completion hints, hidden fields/subcommands)
test/
  integration.zig    # Integration tests (run compiled example binaries, check stdout/stderr)
  consumer/          # Test that zap works as an external package dependency
```

## Testing patterns

### Unit tests (src/)

Tests are embedded in source files using Zig's `test` blocks.

**Help output tests must compare the full output** using `expectEqualStrings`
with multi-line strings. Do not use partial matching (`indexOf`) for help output
tests -- always assert the complete expected output so regressions in formatting,
ordering, or omitted fields are caught.

```zig
try testing.expectEqualStrings(
    \\USAGE: server [options]
    \\
    \\Start the server
    \\
    \\OPTIONS:
    \\  -p, --port            (default: 8080)
    \\  -h, --help             Show help information
    \\
, writer.buffered());
```

### Integration tests (test/integration.zig)

Integration tests run compiled example binaries and check stdout/stderr. These
use `expectStdOutEqual` for exact matches or `expectStdOutMatch` /
`expectStdErrMatch` for substring matches, which is appropriate since they test
end-to-end behavior of full binaries.

### Shell completion tests

Run with `zig build test-shell-completions`. These test actual shell completion
scripts by invoking fish, zsh, and bash with the generated scripts. Requires
`fish`, `zsh`, and `expect` to be installed.

## Key conventions

- Field type determines CLI behavior: `bool` = flag, `u8` (default 0) = counted
  flag, `Positional(T)` = positional, `[]const T` = multi-positional, `?T` =
  optional
- `snake_case` field names become `--kebab-case` CLI options
- `CamelCase` struct names become `kebab-case` subcommand names
- Short flags are auto-assigned from the first character; collisions resolved at
  compile time
- Commands must have a `pub fn run()` or subcommands (enforced at compile time)
